[4] WHO situation report 40
Date: Tue 1 Nov 2022
Source: WHO Uganda [edited]
https://reliefweb.int/report/uganda/uganda-ebola-virus-disease-situation-report-no-40


Uganda Ebola Virus Disease Situation Report No 40
-------------------------------------------------
Key Highlights
--------------
On 20 Sep 2022, the Ministry of Health declared an outbreak of Sudan ebolavirus (SVD) after a case managed at Mubende Regional Referral Hospital (MRRH) in Mubende district was confirmed through testing at the Uganda Virus Research Institute (UVRI). This followed investigations by the National Rapid Response Team of suspicious deaths that had occurred in the district earlier in the month [September 2022]. This is the 1st time in more than a decade that Uganda reports an outbreak of Sudan ebola virus.

• Today [1 Nov 2022] marks 42 days of response to the EVD outbreak, 1st case was confirmed on 19 Sep 2022.
• One newly confirmed EVD case from Kassanda in the past 24 hours, linked to a known case.
• Six newly confirmed deaths in the past 24 hours -- 5 from Mubende, 1 from Entebbe ETU.
• Two new recoveries in the past 24 hours, bringing cumulative recoveries to 45.
• Case Fatality Ratio (CFR) among confirmed cases is 43/130 (33%).
• A total of 1777 contacts actively being followed-up in 10 districts, follow-up rate in the past 24 hours was 87%.

--
